Pin Out Summary¶

Shown below in Figure 12 is a summary of all the Arduino pins.

Figure 12: Arduino Pins Cheat Sheet

Shown below in Table 2 is a summary of all the Arduino Uno specifications.

Table 2: Arduino Uno Specifications
Operating Voltage $5 V$
Input Voltage (recommended) $7$ - $12 V$
Digital I/O Pins 14
PWM Digital I/O Pins 6
Analog Input Pins 6
DC Current per I/O Pin $20 mA$
DC Current for $3.3 V$ Pin $50 mA$
Flash Memory 32KB (minus 0.5KB for bootloader)
SRAM 2KB
EEPROM 1KB
Clock Speed 16MHz

Arduino Language Data Types¶

Shown below in Table 3 are some of the various Arduino language data types.

Table 3: Common Arduino Data Types
Type Possible Values Storage Space
bool
(Boolean, pronounced boo-lee-uhn)		 True or False 1 byte
byte 0 to 255 1 byte
int -32,768 to 32767 2 bytes
float -3.4028235E+38 to 3.4028235E+38 4 bytes
char Stores a character value (i.e. A, B, C, >, %, etc.) 1 byte
array A collection of variables Depends
string An array of char values Depends
